ZH: 我的良心告诉我这是错误的。
EN: My conscience tells me this is wrong.

ZH: 他是一个有良心的人。
EN: He is a person with a conscience.

ZH: 她说她的良心无法容忍这种行为。
EN: She said her conscience couldn't tolerate such behavior.

ZH: 我能安心地睡觉是因为我对别人保持良心。
EN: I can sleep peacefully because I have a clear conscience towards others.

ZH: 良心是我们内心的指南。
EN: Conscience is the compass of our inner self.

ZH: 他的良心不安，因为他知道他犯了一个错误。
EN: His conscience is troubled because he knows he made a mistake.

ZH: 没有良心的人不会有幸福感。
EN: People without a conscience won't experience happiness.

ZH: 对不起，我去年欠你的钱一直让我良心不安。
EN: I'm sorry, the money I owed you last year has been weighing on my conscience.

ZH: 良心的呼唤使我做出了正确的选择。
EN: The call of conscience led me to make the right choice.

ZH: 如果你有良心，你不会对别人撒谎。
EN: If you have a conscience, you won't lie to others.

ZH: 良心是一种道德感知的体现。
EN: Conscience is a reflection of moral perception.

ZH: 这个罪犯不愧是个没有良心的人。
EN: This criminal truly deserves to be called a heartless person.

ZH: 政客应该依赖良心来做出决策。
EN: Politicians should rely on their conscience to make decisions.

ZH: 良心的声音时刻提醒我不要违背道德。
EN: The voice of conscience constantly reminds me not to violate morals.

ZH: 她的良心告诉她帮助那个需要帮助的人。
EN: Her conscience told her to assist the person in need.

ZH: 我希望每个人都能尊重他人的良心。
EN: I hope everyone respects the conscience of others.

ZH: 他经过了良心的斗争，决定承认错误并道歉。
EN: After a struggle of conscience, he decided to admit his mistake and apologize.

ZH: 他的良心感到罪恶，他决定要补偿受害者。
EN: His conscience felt guilty, and he decided to compensate the victim.

ZH: 有一种说法是良心是心灵的镜子。
EN: There is a saying that conscience is the mirror of the soul.

ZH: 我们应该听从内心良心的指引。
EN: We should follow the guidance of our inner conscience.

ZH: 跟随你的良心去做，你不会后悔。
EN: Follow your conscience, and you won't regret it.
